{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week number for the week containing ","type":"text"},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The ISO 8601 week number is the same for every day of the week (from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Moday through Sunday).  That can produce some unusual results"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(described below)."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"getWeekOfYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first week of the year is week 1.  This is the week that contains"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the first Thursday of the year.  Equivalently, this is the first week"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that has more than 4 of its days falling within the calendar year.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The value 0 is never returned by this function.  Days contained","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"within a year but occurring before the first ISO 8601 week of that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"year are considered as being contained in the last week of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"previous year.  Similarly, the final days of a calendar year may be"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"considered as being part of the first ISO 8601 week of the next year"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if 4 or more days of that week are contained within the new year."}],"type":"para